SKIN WITH EROSION AND PURULENT CRUST WITH ADJACENT 
ACANTHOSIS, SEE NOTE 
Note:  These changes are most consistent with 
recent trauma/excoriation.  On the other hand, the 
differential diagnosis would include the 
possibility for the surface of a suppurative 
follicular process surrounded by prurigo changes.  
Clinico-pathologic correlation is recommended.

Collection.Name: A GROSS DESCRIPTION
Collection.ClinicalDescription:
The container is in agreement with the 
requisition. The container is a labeled "4 mm skin 
lesion". Specimen is received in formalin and 
consists of a soft, gray-white, conical skin 
fragment measuring 0.4 x 0.4 x 0.2 cm. Present in 
the center of the skin is a gray-tan irregularity 
measuring 0.4 x 0.3 cm. Margins are inked. 
Bisected along the short axis and entirely 
submitted in cassette A1. SH

Collection.Name: HEMOGLOBIN A1c
Collection.ClinicalDescription:
According to ADA guidelines, hemoglobin A1c <7.0%
represents optimal control in non-pregnant diabetic
patients. Different metrics may apply to specific
patient populations. Standards of Medical Care in
Diabetes-2013. Diabetes Care. 2013;36:s11-s66
 
For the purpose of screening for the presence of
diabetes
<5.7%       Consistent with the absence of diabetes
5.7-6.4%    Consistent with increased risk for diabetes
            (prediabetes)
>or=6.5%    Consistent with diabetes
 
This assay result is consistent with a decreased risk
of diabetes.
 
Currently, no consensus exists for use of hemoglobin
A1c for diagnosis of diabetes for children.
